\h LIGHT \d

\uUSAGE\n
!light lightSource \s[\dtinderbox\s]\d

\uDESCRIPTION\n
Ignite a light source using a tinderbox.
The light source must be in your readied equipment.
You may omit the second argument, in which case the first tinderbox in your inventory will be used.

\uEXAMPLES\n
\qlight torch\d to light your torch (in your readied equipment) using your tinderbox (in your inventory).4`
\qlight \p2#i\qtorch\d to light your second torch.4`
\qlight torch \p2#i\qtinderbox\d to light your torch using your second tinderbox.4`

\uSEE ALSO\n
extinguish, prefixes, refuel
